From {{Sp.}} ''[[latinoamericano]]'', Latin American &gt; {{Sp.}} ''[[latino#Spanish|latino]]'' (''adj''), Latin &gt; {{L.}} ''[[latinus]]'' [http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/latino]

===Proper noun===
'''Latino'''

# A person from Latin America.
# A person residing in the United States, who is of  Latin American descent.
#:''Latinos are quickly becoming the largest minority in the United States.''
# A male Latin Person. Speakers of any of the world's Romance languages spoken in Europe or America.



===Adjective=== 
# of Latin American descent.
# Spanish American adjective latino (feminine: latina) directly translates to English as Latin. Any of the world's Romance languages spoken in Europe or America, or speakers of these languages. i.e.Spaniards view themselves as being Latino, the same as Italians, Romanians, French, Portuguese and people of the Americas who are speakers these languages.

